##I never want to see that number go up again

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

By Chen Xuhou, thepaper.cn

The sad news came again. Wuhan Center Hospital announced on the morning of March 1: Comrade Jiang Xueqing, secretary, director and chief physician of the Party branch of Thyroid and Breast Surgery Department of Wuhan Center Hospital and winner of the Chinese Physicians Award, he died at Wuhan Lung Hospital at 5.32 am on March 1 at the age of 55 after failing to respond to the outbreak.

A week ago on February 23, we said goodbye to Huang Wenjun, Xia SI and Du Xiansheng, three excellent medical staff who died after being infected with new crown pneumonia in the first-line work of fighting the epidemic.

Earlier, the National Health Commission has reported, as of February 11 at 24:00, a total of 1,716 confirmed cases of medical staff reported, including 6 people died in the line of duty.

As of Feb. 24, in the fight against www.thepaper.cn  pneumonia, the _ paper _ reported incomplete statistics, according to official reports and public reports, at least nine doctors and nurses have died from new pneumonia in the outbreak, with the oldest aged 63 and the youngest 29. Of those, seven had contracted the disease before February.

Meanwhile, at least 11 health care workers died in the fight against the disease due to overwork, sudden heart attack, car accident and other reasons.

Some of the 20 people, including the hospital director, led the entire hospital staff in the fight against the epidemic in the first line, after the onset of disease is still busy to transform the hospital to treat patients, and finally completed the hospital renovation as scheduled, he was sent to the intensive-care Unit; Some are village doctors, who remain in their posts in remote rural areas. A 67-year-old village doctor died of an illness in the fight against the epidemic. His son took over his post and continued to fight. Some are doctors born in the 1990s, the 29-year-old husband couldn't cash in on his wife's two-year-old wedding, and the 29-year-old mother left behind a 2-year-old child who didn't know she was dead..

"health is at the mercy of life, " they put into practice, "the oath of Medical Students" in this sentence. And behind them are more than 500,000 health care workers in Hubei who have given up their vacation and are holding their posts. They are nearly 40,000 health care workers who have come from all over the country to support Hubei. They are the vast medical care groups who are fighting to fight the epidemic in the front line of the country, they fought hard to win the battle to defend the epidemic.

Protecting and caring medical workers is an important guarantee for winning the battle against the epidemic, and the Politburo Standing Committee of the Communist Party of China meeting held on February 3 stressed that resources for treatment and protection should be firmly concentrated on the front line of fighting the epidemic, priority is given to meeting the needs of frontline medical staff and patients. The meeting noted that medical personnel will continue to be deployed from the country to assist Wuhan as needed, while protecting the physical and mental health of medical personnel. On February 22, the COVID-19 issued the circular on the full implementation of measures to further protect and care medical workers, ten measures are put forward to further protect the medical staff who care for and care for them. The National Health Commission also issued a notice on February 18 to further strengthen the protection of medical personnel during the epidemic prevention and control in seven aspects.

The paper noted that a series of care policies have also been put in place in many parts of the country for front-line medical staff to fight against NCP. For example, the Guangdong Federation of Trade Unions has set up mental health service teams to provide psychological crisis intervention and psychological counseling services to medical staff and their families in need. Medical staff who are infected with new coronary pneumonia shall be provided with a relief fund of 30,000 yuan each; those who have participated in the medical mutual security scheme for staff and workers on duty may also be given a maximum compensation of 50,000 yuan each.

At the same time, Hubei, Jiangsu Nanjing, Shanxi Datong, Inner Mongolia Baotou, Chongqing, Qinghai, Shandong and other places issued documents, will be given to the fight against the epidemic first-line medical staff children study care policy.

Some of the medical staff who died in the line of duty due to new pneumonia

Jiang Xueqing, Male, 55, secretary, director and chief physician of the Party branch of Thyroid and breast surgery, Wuhan Central Hospital, winner of the Chinese Physicians Award

Comrade Jiang Xueqing was born on March 31,1964 in Wuhan, Hubei Province, according to the announcement of the Wuhan Central Hospital.

After graduating from Tongji Medical University in July 1986, he has been working in Wuhan Central Hospital for more than 30 years as a surgeon. In the hospital during the work, dedicated, patient and meticulous, due diligence for the hospital development has made an important contribution.

Jiang Xueqing died at Wuhan Lung Hospital at 5:32 am on March 1,2020, at the age of 55, after he fell ill during the battle against the new crown pneumonia.

Huang Wenjun, Male, 42, vice director of respiratory medicine, Xiaogan Central Hospital

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In June 2001, Huang Wenjun graduated from the Department of Clinical Medicine of Wuhan University School of Medicine.

He spent a year in respiratory medicine at Huazhong University of Science and Technology from 2004 to 2005, and was recruited as an attending physician in December 2006 and as an associate chief physician in 2012.

I will not shy away from doing it be it weal or woe for me

On the evening of February 23, the official website of Xiaogan City Center Hospital issued an obituary: In the battle against new crown pneumonia, Huang Wenjun was infected and died at 19:30 on February 23.

According to colleagues, January 27, Huang Wenjun said a little dry cough, not very comfortable. Two days later, his condition worsened and he was diagnosed with new crown pneumonia on January 29.

Xiasi, female, 29, resident physician, Department of Gastroenterology, Peking Union Medical College Jiangbei District Hospital

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Concord Jiangbei Hospital issued a notice that in the fight against the epidemic, xiasi unfortunate infection of new crown pneumonia, was admitted on January 19, the hospital fully rescue. On February 7, his condition deteriorated and he was rushed to Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University. At 6:30 on February 23, Xia Si died in Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University.

Shays was born into a family of doctors, her father a military doctor and her mother a nurse. Influenced by her family, she set her sights on becoming a doctor from an early age. She and her husband are both doctors at Concord North Hospital. They both studied medicine at Wuhan Jianghan University and were in love on campus for 11 years, he recalls.

Peng Yinhua, Male, 29, respiratory specialist, Jiangxia District First People's Hospital, Wuhan

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Peng Yinhua and his wife

Peng Yinhua was admitted to Jiangxia District First People's Hospital on January 25 and was admitted to the hospital on January 30. His condition became worse and he was sent to Kam Yin Tam Hospital for treatment. He died at 21:50 on February 20 because his condition deteriorated.

Peng Yinhua was born in a rural family, graduated from Hubei University of Science and Technology Clinical Medical College, resident standardized training for 3 years, in addition to normal work, study, he also part-time hospital 120 emergency work, often send money to parents.

Peng has been married for two years to his wife, who is six months pregnant. He had planned a two-year-late wedding for his wife on February 1, and had invited his colleagues to "have a good time" with unsent invitations in his desk drawer.

Liu Zhiming, Male, 51, director of Wuchang Hospital, Wuhan

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The paper previously reported that in July 1991, Liu Zhiming graduated from the Wuhan University School of Medicine and was assigned to the neurosurgery clinic in the third ward outside the former Yunyang regional people's hospital.

In 1995, Liu Zhiming left Shiyan to work in Wuhan.

Whether in the Yunyang Hospital, the Wuhan Sanyuan or the Wuchang Hospital, Liu Zhiming's fighting strength is almost unknown.

As the director of Wuhan's first designated fever clinic, Liu Zhiming has led all medical staff in the fight against the epidemic since the outbreak. On January 22, Liu Zhiming became ill and was diagnosed with new coronary pneumonia the next day. On January 24, Liu Zhiming was transferred to the intensive-care unit of Wuchang Hospital as his condition worsened. On February 17, Liu Zhiming was in critical condition. On Feb. 18, after 17 hours of ECMO treatment, Liu died.

Liu Fan, female, 59, deputy chief nurse

Liu Fan was working in the injection room of the Community Health Service Centre at Lei Yuen Street, Wuchang Hospital, Wuhan.

Liu was on duty as usual until February 2,2020, according to The@wuhan Post. 3-5 February rotation. At 7 am on February 6, Liu fan called the head nurse of the Department to complain that she was feeling unwell and had fever. The head nurse immediately arranged for her to go to the West Wing of Wuchang Wuhan Hospital for a thorough examination. She was diagnosed with COVID-19 pneumonia on February 7, on the same day, he was admitted to hospital for treatment. During his hospitalization, the hospital tried its best to cure him. However, due to more basic diseases, his condition became progressively worse, and he died at 18:30 on February 14. Before her death, her parents and younger brother also died of new crown pneumonia.

Xiao Jun, Male, 50, deputy chief of General Surgery, Wuhan Red Cross Hospital

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Yangtze daily photo

After graduating from college, Xiao Jun worked at the Wuhan Red Cross Hospital for 29 years. On the evening of February 21, the Wuhan Red Cross Hospital issued a public announcement: Xiao Jun, who was the first line in the fight against the epidemic, was unfortunately infected with new crown pneumonia. He was hospitalized in this hospital on January 26 and transferred to Wuhan's Golden Pool Hospital for treatment on January 27. His condition deteriorated later due to his illness, he died at Kam Yin Tam Hospital in Wuhan at 18:13 on February 8.

Colleagues recalled that Xiao Jun was known as "the little prince of the appendix" because he performed seven or eight appendectomy operations a day, and many patients asked for him by name. Sometimes with relatives and friends to find him, met him out of meetings, patients have to wait for him to come back.

Li Wenliang, Male, 35, ophthalmologist, Wuhan Central Hospital

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Li, who took the Gaokao in 2004 and graduated from the Wuhan University with a seven-year degree in clinical medicine, worked in Xiamen for three years before returning to Wuhan in 2014 to work at the Wuhan Central Hospital.

On January 8,2020, Li Wenliang was admitted to the hospital with an unknown viral pneumonia patient and was infected. He died at 2:58 am on February 7 after being caught in an outbreak of COVID-19 pneumonia, according to information released by Wuhan's Central Hospital.

Du Xiansheng, Male, 54, doctor of Hainan Qiongzhong Yangjiang Farm Hospital

According to the Hainan daily, on January 18, Du Xiansheng developed fever, cough and other symptoms at work, and self-medication for 2 days. He was admitted to Danzhou People's Hospital on January 22 because his condition did not improve. He was suspected to have been infected by COVID-19. On 25 January, he was diagnosed with COVID-19 pneumonia and immediately transferred from Danzhou Municipal People's Hospital to Hainan Provincial People's Hospital. At noon on February 23, Du Xiansheng died in vain.

The paper reported earlier that Du Xiansheng was one of the patients in the local outbreak at the Yangjiang Farm Hospital, where he had been treated by Jia mou, the head of the hospital's Prevention and protection team, jia was in close contact with Zeng, whose parents traveled to Wuhan in early January. As of January 29, two confirmed cases of local pneumonia with COVID-19 infection have been reported in Hainan Province, namely Du (Du Xiansheng) and Jia, according to a notice issued by the Health Commission of Hainan Province.

Some of the medical staff who died from other causes

Wang Tucheng, male, 37, village doctor of Xinwangzhuang village, Dong village, Changge, Henan Province

Wang Tu, a doctor from Xinwangzhuang village in Dong village, Changge, Henan Province, suffered an acute myocardial infarction on Feb. 10 due to overwork, Chinanews.com reported. He was only 37.

Wang Tucheng graduated from Changge Health School in 1999 and obtained the village doctor qualification certificate in 2005. Since then, he has been working in the new Wangzhuang village clinic. Wang Tucheng, who has been fighting against the new pneumonia for many days, has set up his bedroom in the village clinic in order to keep his family in a "fighting" state all day long.

Jiang Jijun, Male, 51, doctor of infection department, Taizhou People's Hospital, Jiangsu Province

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
According to the Southern Metropolis Daily, on Jan. 23, Dr. Jiang died after failing to resuscitate him after he collapsed from respiratory arrest as he rushed to a fever clinic after rounds.

During the course of rescuing Dr. Jiang Jijun, the experts basically determined that the sudden death was caused by cardiovascular and cerebrovascular causes.

Jiang Jijun was deputy chief physician, engaged in infectious disease diagnosis and treatment for more than 20 years, unknown causes of fever waiting for investigation has rich clinical experience.

Jiang Jinbo, Male, 58, physician, Center for Disease Control and Prevention, Dayu County, Jiangxi Province

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Jiang Jinbo (first from left) , Jiangxi, China

Jiang Jinbo died on Jan. 28 after working for days on the front line of the epidemic, suffering a heart attack due to overwork, the Jiangxi daily reported. His last day of lunch was instant noodles; his last moments of life were spent thinking about work.

After graduating from the Ganzhou Medical School in 1982, he worked for the Dayu County CDC, after 2003 SARS, 2009 Dayu "73" floods, 2013 bird flu, 2019 human infection of Streptococcus suis disease and other major epidemic "campaign" , has been repeatedly rated as advanced health system individuals.

Xu Hui, 51, deputy director of Nanjing Hospital of Traditional Chinese medicine

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xu died at 00:03 on Feb. 7 after 18 days of fighting to prevent and control the outbreak, according to the wechat public account "Nanjing News" .

Xu Hui is very busy. She is not only the deputy director of the Nanjing Chinese Medicine Hospital's pneumonia prevention and control headquarters, but also the head of the hospital's prevention and control working group. In the 18 days of fighting against the epidemic, she led the formulation of the "Nanjing Hospital of Traditional Chinese Medicine COVID-19 pneumonia emergency plan" , the formation of fever clinics, pre-check triage medical team, to raise materials for prevention and control..

Mao Xianhong, Male, 52, deputy director of Central Health Center, Xianyang town, Pucheng County, Nanping City, Fujian Province

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Mao Xianghong checked the body temperature of passengers at a high-speed checkpoint on Jan. 25, CCTV reported. After 9:00 pm that night, a car saw the signal through here, mistakenly will the accelerator when the brake, causing the vehicle out of control, hit mao-like red, after the rescue invalid death.

According to family members, the day was not mao-like red on duty. Because the hospital is understaffed, Mao Zedong red volunteered to work overtime. Did Not expect an accident, in the New Year's Day fell in the line of epidemic prevention.

Song Yingjie, Male, 28, deputy group leader of Pharmaceutical Group, Maji Health Center, Donghu Town, Hengshan County, Hunan Province

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Since the beginning of the Lunar New Year, Songyingjie has spent several days at the intersection of the Yue Lin Expressway and the East L. Expressway to screen people and check their body temperature, chinanews.com reported.

In the early hours of February 3, he and his colleagues returned to their dormitory at the hospital after a shift at a highway junction.

The same afternoon, Song Yingjie was found in the hospital dormitory sudden death.

Mount Heng County Propaganda Department said Song Yingjie in the fight against COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic, many days of continuous overwork, due to overwork caused sudden cardiac death, died in the line of duty.

Wei Anjun, Male, 67, Xiaoji village doctor, Longwang, Xiangzhou District, Hubei

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wei was the village doctor in Xiao Ji Village, Longwang, Xiangzhou District, Xiangyang, and has been the head of four groups in Xiao Ji village since 2012, Hubei Daily reported. After the outbreak of the new crown pneumonia epidemic, he volunteered to fight day and night for 14 consecutive days at the epidemic prevention and control point in Xiaoji to Wenwan village to overcome the difficulties of simple protective measures, weak awareness of villagers'prevention and control, less personnel with heavy tasks, etc. , adhere to the round-the-clock garrison points, temperature, have persuaded back more than 300 people, because of excessive fatigue in the anti-epidemic front, died after rescue invalid.

After Wei's death, his son Wei took his place. "More than a decade ago, I passed the relevant qualification certificate and took over as a village doctor from my father, " Wei said. "Now, I will continue to take over from my father and fight on the front line to fight the epidemic. "

Zhu Zhengrong, Male, 48, Ward Leader of Community Health Service Center in Nanyang town, Qidong city, Nantong City, Jiangsu Province

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Jiangsu net map of China

On Feb. 22, Zhu Zhengrong died despite multiple organ dysfunction syndrome attempts to revive him, according to the Health Commission of Qidong City. Born in May 1973, Zhu Zhengrong joined the work force in August 1996 and joined the party in November 2017. He has won the honorary titles of "top ten doctor" and "outstanding Communist Party member" of Qidong Health and hygiene system.

Zhu Zhengrong, who discovered Takayasu arteritis years ago after the new pneumonia outbreak, hid the notice and led the entire ward team into the battle against the disease. In order to overcome the difficulty of less people and more work, he took the initiative to take responsibility. While he was on duty in the ward, he was also on duty at the fever clinic. He began working one after another from New Year's Eve. For more than 20 days, he was always on the front line of Epidemic Prevention and control.

Chen Jian, 26, village doctor of Cun Tian Village, Kuixiang Township, Yiliang County, Zhaotong City, Yunnan Province

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Chinanews.com

Chen Jian, Han, junior college culture, joined the Cuntian village clinic in Kuixiang township in April 2017 to work as a village doctor, she has been responsible for maternal health management, child health management, health supervision and coordination services and basic medical services, and other United States Public Health Service projects.

According to Chinanews.com, Chi Huanqin and Chen Jian were responsible for medical monitoring of Xinfang, Houshan, Zhongjie and other home observation groups in Cuntian village, according to the Kuixiang hospital after the outbreak of the epidemic. At around 10:00 on February 12, Chen Jian rode an electric bicycle with Chi Huanqin, after conducting body temperature monitoring and epidemic prevention propaganda on the home observation subjects of the Cuntian Village Street Group, the Xinfang Group and the Houshan Group, when walking to the "Li Jia Wan Zi" of the SUMAC group in Cuntian village, they bumped into a stone tablet about 2 meters from the road surface, resulting in injuries to different degrees. They were then sent to the hospital.

Among them, Chen Jian died at 3:45 pm on the 12th due to serious injuries; Chi was transferred to the Emergency Department of Yiliang County, Zhaotong People's Hospital.

Song Yunhua, 46, Doctor, Taiping Community Clinic, Qinghua Street, Longyang district, Baoshan, Yunnan Province

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Bright Net

According to reports from Kwangmyong, on January 31, Dr. Song Yunhua, who had been working on the prevention and control of the epidemic of new crown pneumonia for one morning, was on his way to No. 1 Shenguanyuan, Qinghua Street, Longyang district, Baoshan, when he was struck by a car accident at about 13:30. The rescue was ineffective, unfortunately, he died

The News of Dr. Song's death was hard for those who knew her. "She worked with us at the community entrance for more than four hours the day before yesterday, " said Yang Hu, Taiping's community secretary, "and worked hard to check out foreigners for the safety of the masses, " Kwangmyong reported. Bai Zuqin, a resident of Taiping Community, said, "Dr. Song has been caring for us all these years. Today she is gone, and we have lost one of our closest friends. "

Zhang Jianhua, male, 50, head of public health section and ambulance driver, Qiupotou Town Health Center, Xunyi County, Xianyang province, Shaanxi Province

Since joining the work force, Zhang Jianhua has been sticking to the front line of Rural Public Health, responsible for public health, chronic diseases, residents'health records, health care and poverty alleviation in Qiupatou town, Xunyi County, Xianyang province, according to cnr.cn, he was also responsible for the vaccination of more than 6,000 families. He was repeatedly rated as a "health guard" by the Xunyi County Health Bureau and was awarded as an advanced worker in Xunyi County health system for six consecutive years.

In January 2020, in the face of a sudden outbreak of new pneumonia, comrade Zhang Jianhua, who had not yet completed his sick leave, responded positively to the call and returned to work ahead of schedule, it has undertaken the task of epidemic prevention and control propaganda in all units of the town and at 12 checkpoints in 7 villages. For more than 20 days, he has been working on the front line of Epidemic Prevention and control, working more than 10 hours a day.

February 3,2020, Zhang Jianhua in the town of Qiupatou finance station disinfection on the way to a sudden coma, died after rescue invalid.
